obo:GO_0099524  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_883  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: The paper is describing the expression pattern of Ca2+ binding proteins in the calyx of Held synapse using conventional immunostaining. The calyx of Held is a giant synapse where a clear separation of can be made between the pre and postsynaptic compartments using standard confocal microscopy.\nFigure 6 describes the results of a double immuostaining for Rab3 (a presynaptic marker) and calbindin. The staining for calbindin is restricted to the postsynaptic compartment, diffused (Fig. 6A), and does not co-localize with the Rab3 staining (Figure 6B,C).\n\n1/7/2017 Pim\nCytosolic localization is inferred from the diffuse staining of the protein.. Experimental description: 'Figure 6... Results from double-labelling of an MNTB section from a\nP10 rat, incubated with anti Rab-3A and anti-CB antibodies, are shown.'" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" ;
        dc:date           "2017-07-01" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_883" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

